    "AnthropomorphismIn this section we explore the phenomenon of anthropomorphism as one of the mechanisms which is driving and enabling the current AI hype as outlined in section one.",
    "Anthropomorphism has been widely studied in relation to AI and many attempts have been made to conceptualise, measure and theorise the phenomenon [34].",
    "One of the most commonly used definitions is offered by Epley et al. [35] and states that anthropomorphism involves attributing human characteristics (e.g.",
    "intentions, motivations, and emotions) to the behaviour of nonhuman entities, such as animals, natural forces, deities, and machines, whether they are real or imagined (pp. 864-865).",
